<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>543</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0029</addr>  <route>axt-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Pseudocontinuous <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> is called <b>pseudocontinuous</b> if there is
  a specified function giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the mere existence of a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the following
  conditions.
  <ul>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</tex>.</li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>544</anchor>   <addr>axt-002M</addr>  <route>axt-002M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author> </authors> <title>Terminology for domain theory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  In <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">Tom de Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link> and his Agda formalization of domain
  theory, the term ‚Äústructurally continuous‚Äù is used to mean a
  <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> equipped with a function giving, for every <tex>x :
  D</tex>, a small directed family of elements way below <tex>x</tex>, giving <tex>x</tex> as its
  join.
</p><p>  In the new terminology, this notion of ‚Äústructure‚Äù involved in the continuity
  of a dcpo is made explicit by the following notion.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>545</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002H</addr>  <route>axt-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Continuity datum for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em>continuity datum</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is a function
  giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, a specified <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,
   \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the following conditions.
  <ol>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</tex>.</li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  Factoring this structure out into a definition of its own obviates the need to
  have a name for the notion of a ‚Äú<tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo having a specified continuity
  datum‚Äù, which is what ‚Äústructurally continuous‚Äù means. Even though the
  equivalence between <link href="axt-0027.xml" type="local" title="Unintentionally left blank">structurally continuous</link> and ‚Äúhaving a
  specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>‚Äù is completely trivial, we still record
  this in the following proposition to be able to explicitly refer to this
  terminological identity.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>546</anchor>  <taxon>Proposition</taxon> <addr>axt-001K</addr>  <route>axt-001K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>24</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author> </authors>  <meta name="source"><b>Defn 4.4.1</b> of <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">de Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">PhD thesis</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> having a specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>  is the same thing as <tex>D</tex> being <link href="axt-0027.xml" type="local" title="Unintentionally left blank">structurally continuous</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  By replacing the specified existence here with mere existence, we obtain the
  notion of a <link href="axt-002I.xml" type="local" title="Continuous V-dcpo">continuous <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link>. The terminology for this is
  unchanged (i.e. is the same as the terminology of <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">Tom de Jong</link>'s
  <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link>).
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>547</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002I</addr>  <route>axt-002I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Continuous <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> is called <em>continuous</em> if there exists a
  <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link> for it.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>548</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0029</addr>  <route>axt-0029.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Pseudocontinuous <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> is called <b>pseudocontinuous</b> if there is
  a specified function giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the mere existence of a
  <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> satisfying the following
  conditions.
  <ul>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)  \ll  x</tex>.</li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>549</anchor>  <taxon>Remark</taxon> <addr>axt-0031</addr>  <route>axt-0031.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> being pseudocontinuous is the same thing as it
  having a specified <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>, but with the specified
  existence requirement in the notion of <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link> relaxed to
  requirement of mere existence.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>550</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002D</addr>  <route>axt-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> with the further requirement that
  for every <tex>x : D</tex>, the directed <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex>  given by the basis satisfies the condition
  <tex display="block">\forall  k : K_x. \  \beta ( \kappa _x(k))  \ll  x.</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>551</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002E</addr>  <route>axt-002E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional continuous basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>extensional continuous basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-002D.xml" type="local" title="Intensional continuous basis for a V-dcpo">intensional continuous basis</link> that is <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb></trail> <anchor>552</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002B</addr>  <route>axt-002B.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraicity datum for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>algebraicity datum</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is a function
  giving, for every <tex>x : D</tex>, a specified <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link>  <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> on <tex>D</tex> that satisfies the following.
  <ol>    <li>The family <tex>(K_x,  \kappa _x)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>x =  \bigvee ^{ \uparrow }_{k : K_x}  \kappa _x(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>For each <tex>k : K_x</tex>, <tex>\kappa _x(k)</tex> is compact.</li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  Similar to the case of a <link href="axt-002H.xml" type="local" title="Continuity datum for a V-dcpo">continuity datum</link>, we record the
  terminological identity between a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> being
  <link href="axt-001C.xml" type="local" title="Structural algebraicity of a dcpo">‚Äústructurally algebraic‚Äù</link> (the terminology from <link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local" title="Tom de Jong">de
  Jong</link>'s <link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">thesis</link>) and it having a specified
  <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity datum</link>.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>553</anchor>  <taxon>Proposition</taxon> <addr>axt-002A</addr>  <route>axt-002A.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors>  </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> having a specified <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity
  datum</link> is the same thing as <tex>D</tex> being <link href="axt-001C.xml" type="local" title="Structural algebraicity of a dcpo">structurally
  algebraic</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>10</crumb></trail> <anchor>554</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001L</addr>  <route>axt-001L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>24</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraic <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is called <em>algebraic</em> if there exists an
  <link href="axt-002B.xml" type="local" title="Algebraicity datum for a V-dcpo">algebraicity datum</link> for it.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>11</crumb></trail> <anchor>555</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002C</addr>  <route>axt-002C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Algebraic <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> (alternative)</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>D</tex> be a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> and define the type
  <tex display="block">K_x   \vcentcolon \equiv   \sum _{c : D}{ \mathsf{isCompact} ( c )   \times  c  \sqsubseteq  x}</tex> of
  compact elements below a given <tex>x : D</tex>. The <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is
  called <em>algebraic</em> if it satisfies the following conditions.
  <ul>    <li>For every <tex>x : D</tex>, <tex>K_x</tex> is <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-small.</li>    <li>The <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> <tex>(K_x,  \mathsf{pr} _1 )</tex> is directed with supremum <tex>x</tex>.</li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>12</crumb></trail> <anchor>556</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002F</addr>  <route>axt-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional algebraic basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>intensional algebraic basis</em> for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo <tex>D</tex> is an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional
  basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> satisfying
  <tex display="block">\forall  b : B. \  \mathsf{isCompact} ( \beta (b) ) .</tex></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>13</crumb></trail> <anchor>557</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002G</addr>  <route>axt-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>29</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional algebraic basis for a <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <em>extensional algebraic basis</em> for a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</link> <tex>D</tex> is an
  <link href="axt-002F.xml" type="local" title="Intensional algebraic basis for a V-dcpo">intensional algebraic basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> that is
  <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>558</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0021</addr>  <route>axt-0021.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>26</day></date> <authors><author><link href="tom-de-jong.xml" type="local">Tom de Jong</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</title> <meta name="source"><b>Defn. 3.2.7</b> of (<link href="tdj-thesis.xml" type="local" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations">[TdJ]</link>, <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/DomainTheory.Basics.Dcpo.html#4941" type="external"><tex>\dagger</tex></link>)</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  Let <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex> be a universe. A poset <tex>D</tex> is a <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-dcpo</em> if the join of
  of every <link href="axt-001F.xml" type="local" title="ùì•-Family"><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family</link> on set <tex>D</tex> exists in <tex>D</tex>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>559</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-001F</addr>  <route>axt-001F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author>Ayberk Tosun</author> </authors> <title>ùì•-Family</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <em><tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>-family on a type <tex>A :  \mathcal{U}</tex></em> is a pair <tex>(I,  \iota )</tex> where
  <ul>    <li><tex>I</tex> is a type in universe <tex>\mathcal{V}</tex>,</li>    <li>and <tex>\iota</tex> is a function of type <tex>I  \to  A</tex>.</li>  </ul></p><p>  List of formal definitions:
  <ol>    <li>      <link href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk//~mhe/TypeTopology/Slice.Family.html#262" type="external">Fam in UF.Slice</link>      in TypeTopology.
    </li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>560</anchor>   <addr>axt-002P</addr>  <route>axt-002P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Terminology for locale theory</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>14</crumb></trail> <anchor>561</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002Q</addr>  <route>axt-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Spectral locale in UF</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0008.xml" type="local" title="Frame (type-theoretic)"><tex>( \mathcal{U} ,  \mathcal{V} ,  \mathcal{W} )</tex>-locale</link> <tex>X</tex> is called <b>spectral</b>  if it satisfies the following three conditions.
  <ol>    <li>It is a compact locale (i.e. the empty meet is compact).</li>    <li>The meet of two compact opens is compact.</li>    <li>      For every <tex>U :  \mathcal{O} ( X )</tex>, there exists a directed <tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-family
      <tex>(K_U,  \kappa _U)</tex> that satisfies the following conditions.
      <ol>        <li><tex>(K_U,  \kappa _U)</tex> is directed.</li>        <li><tex>U =  \bigvee _{k : K_U}  \kappa _U(k)</tex>.</li>        <li>          It consists of compact opens i.e.
          <tex>\forall  k : K_U. \  \mathsf{isCompact} ( \kappa _{U}(k) )</tex>.
        </li>      </ol>    </li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree><p>  Notice the relationship of the third condition here to
  <link href="axt-0029.xml" type="local" title="Pseudocontinuous V-dcpo">pseudocontinuity</link>. If we formulate a notion of ‚Äúpseudoalgebraicity‚Äù
  i.e. the analogue of <link href="axt-0029.xml" type="local" title="Pseudocontinuous V-dcpo">pseudocontinuity</link> for
  <link href="axt-001L.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic V-dcpo">algebraicity</link>, we could use that to avoid the repetition here
  because they are exactly the same thing. This is not good for presentation
  purposes (as for as locale theory is concerned), however, so it should
  probably be recorded as an equivalence.
</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>15</crumb></trail> <anchor>562</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0032</addr>  <route>axt-0032.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Intensional spectral basis for a locale</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <b>intensional spectral basis</b> for a <link href="axt-0008.xml" type="local" title="Frame (type-theoretic)"><tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-locale</link>  <tex>X</tex> is an <link href="axt-0022.xml" type="local" title="Intensional basis for a V-dcpo">intensional basis</link> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> for the frame
  <tex>\mathcal{O} ( X )</tex> (considered as a <link href="axt-0021.xml" type="local" title="V-dcpo"><tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-dcpo</link>) that satisfies the
  following two conditions
  <ul>    <li>For every <tex>b : B</tex>, <tex>\beta (b)</tex> is a <link href="axt-002S.xml" type="local" title="Compact open of a locale in UF">compact open</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</li>    <li>      The basis <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> is closed under finite meets. This is to say
      that it satisfies the following conditions.
      <ul>        <li>It contains the empty meet: <tex>\exists  t : B. \  \mathsf{isTop} ( \beta (t))</tex>.</li>        <li>          It is closed under binary meets:
          <tex display="block">\forall  b_1, b_2 : B. \  \exists  b_3 : B \  \beta (b_3) \  \text{is the glb of} \  \{   \beta (b_2),  \beta (b_3)  \} .</tex>        </li>      </ul>    </li>  </ul></p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>16</crumb></trail> <anchor>563</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-0033</addr>  <route>axt-0033.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Extensional spectral basis for a locale</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  An <b>extensional spectral basis</b> <tex>(B,  \beta )</tex> for a
  <link href="axt-0008.xml" type="local" title="Frame (type-theoretic)"><tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-locale</link> is an <link href="axt-0032.xml" type="local" title="Intensional spectral basis for a locale">intensional spectral basis</link> that is
  <link href="axt-0028.xml" type="local" title="Extensional basis for a V-dcpo">extensional</link>.
</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>17</crumb></trail> <anchor>564</anchor>  <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>axt-002R</addr>  <route>axt-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="ayberkt.xml" type="local">Ayberk Tosun</link></author><author><link href="martin-escardo.xml" type="local">Mart√≠n H. Escard√≥</link></author> </authors> <title>Zero-dimensional locale in UF</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>  A <link href="axt-0008.xml" type="local" title="Frame (type-theoretic)"><tex>( \mathcal{U} ,  \mathcal{V} ,  \mathcal{W} )</tex>-locale</link> <tex>X</tex> is called
  <b>zero-dimensional</b> if it satisfies the following condition:
  for every <tex>U :  \mathcal{O} ( X )</tex>, there exists a directed <tex>\mathcal{W}</tex>-family <tex>(K_U,
   \kappa _U)</tex> that satisfies the following conditions.
  <ol>    <li><tex>(K_U,  \kappa _U)</tex> is directed.</li>    <li><tex>U =  \bigvee _{k : K_U}  \kappa _U(k)</tex>.</li>    <li>      It consists of clopens i.e.
      <tex>\forall  k : K_U. \  \mathsf{isClopen} ( \kappa _{U}(k))</tex>.
    </li>  </ol></p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>